 What is an Object  (2)<body>
  What is an Object  (2)  
    What is an Object  (2) 

    An object  exists in time and space  has crisply defined conceptual boundaries  may be tangible or intangible  Person, program, bank account, sales order, linked list    Definition: An object  has state  exhibits some well-defined behavior  has a unique identity    The structure and behavior of similar objects are defined in their common class  An object is an instance of some class  We use the terms object and instance interchangeably         
 
   

